{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox LGBT rights | location_header = Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha | image = LocationStHelena.png | caption = [[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]] | legal_status = Legal | military = UK responsible for defense (Since 2000) | gender_identity_expression = | recognition_of_relationships = Same-sex marriage legal since 2017 | adoption = Yes since 2017 | discrimination_protections = Yes (on the basis of sexual orientation only), since 2009 }}
'''LGBT rights''' in [[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]] have gradually evolved over the years. Discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation is banned in the entire territory through the ''Constitution Order 2009'' and [[same-sex marriage]] has been legal on the islands since 2017.<ref name="CProtection">[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2009/1751/schedule/made The St Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha Constitution Order 2009]</ref>
==Legality of same-sex sexual activity== [[Homosexuality]] is legal in [[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]]. Same-sex sexual acts were expressly decriminalised under the UK's ''Caribbean Territories (Criminal Law) Order, 2000''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/news/articles/2005-13634.html |title=MPs criticise Cayman Islands’ draft constitution for omitting gay rights |publisher=Pink News |date= |accessdate=19 January 2011}}</ref>
==Recognition of same-sex relationships== {{Main|Same-sex marriage in Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha}} [[Same-sex marriage]] has been legal on [[Ascension Island]] since 1 January 2017,<ref>{{cit web|url=http://www.sainthelena.gov.sh/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX-GAZ-No-111-2016-Legislation.pdf|title=The St. Helena Government Gazette No 111 2016|date=23 December 2016|work=Ascension Island Government|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104162951/http://www.sainthelena.gov.sh/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX-GAZ-No-111-2016-Legislation.pdf|archivedate=4 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascension-island.gov.ac/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LN-6-Marriage-AscensionCommencement-Order-2016.pdf|title=Marriage (Ascension) (Commencement) Order, 2016|date=1 January 2017|work=Ascension Island Government|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113171028/http://www.ascension-island.gov.ac/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LN-6-Marriage-AscensionCommencement-Order-2016.pdf|archivedate=14 January 2017}}</ref> on [[Tristan da Cunha]] since 4 August 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/lisaphillips07/status/893474155089285122|title=Ascension Marriage Ordinance now extended to Tristan da Cunha. This means same sex marriage in both islands is enshrined in law|publisher=Twitter|first=Lisa|last=Phillips|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=4 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804203136/https://twitter.com/lisaphillips07/status/893474155089285122|archivedate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sainthelena.gov.sh/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX-GAZ-No-57-2017-Legislation_TDC-.pdf|title=The St. Helena Government Gazette No. 57 of 2017|publisher=Government of Saint Helena|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=4 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804203042/http://www.sainthelena.gov.sh/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX-GAZ-No-57-2017-Legislation_TDC-.pdf|archivedate=4 August 2017}}</ref> and since 20 December 2017 on [[Saint Helena]].<ref>[http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2017/12/20/this-tiny-island-just-passed-same-sex-marriage/ This tiny island just passed same-sex marriage]</ref>
==Discrimination protections== The ''St Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha Constitution Order 2009'' bans discrimination based on sexual orientation.<ref name="CProtection" />
==Adoption and parenting== Under the ''Saint Helena Welfare of Children Ordinance 2010'' (which applies to Saint Helena and Tristan da Cunha) and the ''Ascension Island Child Welfare Ordinance 2011'' (which applies to Ascension Island), only married couples may adopt. Same-sex couples may marry in the territory, therefore they also have the right to adopt. Local agencies, in the case of an adoption, follow the letter of the law with the best interest and the views of the child.<ref>[http://www.sainthelena.gov.sh/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Welfare-of-Children-Ord-310712.pdf WELFARE OF CHILDREN ORDINANCE]</ref><ref>[http://www.ascension-island.gov.ac/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Child-Welfare-Ordinance-20111.pdf CHILD WELFARE ORDINANCE 2011]</ref>
According to a 2006 UK Government report, there have been no adoptions in Saint Helena or Ascension Island for many years.<ref>UNITED KINGDOM OVERSEAS TERRITORIES AND CROWN DEPENDENCIES, "This report sets out the progress made in the UK’s Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies in implementing the Convention on the Rights of the Child since 1999, ''OHCHR''</ref>
