'''Thomas Colapietro''' (born 1940) is a former [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[Connecticut Senate|Connecticut State Senator]] who represented [[Bristol, Connecticut|Bristol]], [[Plainville, Connecticut|Plainville]], [[Plymouth, Connecticut|Plymouth]], and part of [[Harwinton, Connecticut|Harwinton]].

He was born and lives in [[Bristol, Connecticut]].<ref>[http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/7101/thomas-colapietro-jr#.WG64zZpDTIUThomas Colapietro, Jr.'s Biography - The Voter's Self Defense System - Vote Smart] Retrieved 2017-01-05.</ref>

In February 2004, he made homophobic remarks for which he apologized after public outrage.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}

