{{Orphan|date=September 2010}}

A '''write out''' is a [[punishment]] used in [[school]]s in which a misbehaving [[student]] must write something out. It is different from writing lines as, instead of writing something out a number of times, the student might write out a [[page (paper)|page]], [[chapter (books)|chapter]] or [[paragraph]] of their schoolbook, workbook or [[novel]]. In the case of non-written homework ([[spelling]]s), the student might have to write the spellings a number of times.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.investopedia.com/terms/w/writeout.asp|title=Write Out|last=Staff|first=Investopedia|date=2006-11-09|work=Investopedia|access-date=2018-08-11|language=en-US}}</ref>

